  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "This is the follow-up issue for what was just discussed with some swarm members on the swarm summit in Berlin.\r\nIt would be great to expose the swarm API (like done here: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/tree/master/mobile) to be able to easily use it from android.\r\n\r\nWould open the following required APIs/use-cases in the order of importance:\r\n - get the contract-ABI for contract-addresses (to render user interface and interact with the contract)\r\n - get the natspec (https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/Ethereum-Natural-Specification-Format) to better render the userinterface (not that important in the beginning but for later in the process)\r\n - read data from swarm - to create a reading content-provider (https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/providers/content-provider-creating.html)\r\n - write content to swarm (my main use case here to migrate https://github.com/ligi/Satoshiproof to Swarm+ETH)\r\nAlso a move to the Rinkeby testnet would be nice ",
